---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="RFC Process" description="How to propose and advance new SANE standards through the RFC process.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>RFC - Request for Comments</h1>
      <p>The open process for proposing, discussing, and ratifying SANE standards.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-medium">

      <div class="rfc-box">
        <h3>Ready to propose a standard?</h3>
        <p>
          Open a GitHub issue using the RFC template. Anyone can propose; the community discusses;
          consensus drives ratification.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-1">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/sane-av/sane-av.github.io/issues/new?template=rfc.yml"
            target="_blank" rel="noopener"
            class="btn btn-primary"
          >
            Open an RFC Issue →
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>How the Process Works</h2>

      <div class="steps">
        {[
          { step: '1', title: 'Proposal', body: 'Open a GitHub issue using the RFC template. Describe the problem, proposed solution, and affected AV domains.' },
          { step: '2', title: 'Discussion', body: 'The community reviews the RFC. Comments, concerns, and proposed amendments are discussed openly on the issue.' },
          { step: '3', title: 'Draft PR', body: 'Once rough consensus is reached, open a Pull Request with the draft standard document in Markdown format.' },
          { step: '4', title: 'Review Period', body: 'The PR enters a minimum 14-day public review. Major changes restart the clock.' },
          { step: '5', title: 'Ratification', body: 'After review with no blocking objections, the PR is merged. The standard is published with status: published.' },
        ].map(({ step, title, body }) => (
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-number">{step}</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="step-title">{title}</h3>
              <p class="step-body">{body}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2>RFC Statuses</h2>
      <table class="mt-1">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="status-badge status-draft">draft</span></td><td>Work in progress, not ready for review</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="status-badge status-review">review</span></td><td>In the 14-day public review period</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="status-badge status-published">published</span></td><td>Ratified and recommended for implementation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="status-badge status-deprecated">deprecated</span></td><td>Superseded by a newer standard</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="mt-3">Principles</h2>
      <ul class="prose mt-1">
        <li><strong>Rough consensus, not unanimity.</strong> We seek broad agreement, not perfection.</li>
        <li><strong>Technical merit first.</strong> Arguments backed by evidence and real-world data carry more weight.</li>
        <li><strong>No IP encumbrances.</strong> All standards must be implementable freely without patent licensing fees.</li>
        <li><strong>Plain English.</strong> Write for the working AV professional, not just academics.</li>
        <li><strong>Versioned and auditable.</strong> Every change is in Git. Nothing is ever quietly altered.</li>
      </ul>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
